pr_review_comment_body:
This doesn't seem very Pythonic; why not
```python
try:
    value = int(value)
except ValueError:
    try:
        value = float(value)
    except ValueError:
        pass
```

these lines can be simplified with the `while...else` syntax as below:
```
while self._send_futures:
    f, kind, kwargs, msg = self._send_futures.pop(0)
    if not f.done():
        break
else:
     return
```

As a side comment, the Pythonic way to use bool arguments is, for example, `if left_right:`. In which case a different renaming is suggested: `if horizontal_alignment:`. But as I mentioned before, I would prefer:

```python
if alignment == 'horizontal':
    ...
elif alignment == 'vertical':
    ...
else:
    raise ValueError('incorrect value for alignment: %s' % alignment)
```

